This paper belongs to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category as it focuses on investigating the performance of web-testing tools to provide empirical evidence supporting choices in software test tool selection and configuration. The paper also discusses the choice of programming language and browser, which could fall under Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Computer Systems Organization (cs.CE) sub-categories, respectively. Additionally, the paper mentions stability as a factor, which could be related to Software Development (cs.SD) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
